Description: Tools for RMST-based study design and analysis planning. Provides
    power and sample size calculations for two-arm studies using direct RMST
    modeling approaches from the biostatistical literature, including
    semiparametric additive models with splines from Zhang and Schaubel (2024)
    <doi:10.1002/bimj.202200371>, linear IPCW-based models from Tian, Zhao,
    and Wei (2014) <doi:10.1093/biostatistics/kxt050>, multiplicative
    stratified models from Wang et al. (2019) <doi:10.1002/sim.8356>, and
    covariate-dependent censoring methods from Wang and Schaubel (2018)
    <doi:10.1007/s10985-017-9391-6>.
